1. Introduction
Welcome to Customers Mart. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our application. Please read this policy carefully to understand how we manage your personal and organizational data.

2. Information We Collect
We may collect and process the following types of information:

Personal Information: Information you provide when registering or logging into the app, such as your name, email address, phone number, and organization details.
Inventory Data: Information about items, categories, stock levels, purchase orders, sales records, and supplier or customer details.
Usage Data: Details about how you interact with the app, such as pages viewed, actions performed, and feature usage.
Device Information: Data about your device, including the device type, operating system, IP address, and app version.
3. How We Use Your Information
We use the information collected for the following purposes:

To manage and maintain your inventory records
To provide and enhance app features for inventory tracking, stock alerts, and reporting
To personalize your experience and improve usability
To send notifications, updates, and critical service-related communications
To detect and prevent fraud, technical issues, or unauthorized access
4. Sharing of Information
We do not sell or rent your personal or inventory data to third parties. However, we may share information in the following cases:

With Service Providers: We may share your data with third-party service providers to support functions such as app hosting, data backup, and analytics.
For Legal Compliance: If required by law or legal processes, we may disclose your data to regulatory authorities or other third parties.
With Your Consent: We may share data with third parties if you have explicitly authorized us to do so.
5. Data Security
We implement reasonable security measures to protect your data from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. However, no system can guarantee absolute security. We encourage you to use strong passwords and maintain the confidentiality of your login credentials.

6. Your Rights
Depending on your location, you may have certain rights regarding your data, such as:

Accessing, updating, or deleting your personal information
Exporting your inventory data
Restricting or objecting to certain processing activities
Withdrawing consent where applicable
To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at [Your Contact Email].

7. Retention of Data
We retain your information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this policy unless a longer retention period is required by law.

8. Childrenâ€™s Privacy
Our app is not designed for children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If we discover that a child under 13 has provided personal information, we will promptly delete it.

9. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted here, and we will notify you of significant updates through email or in-app notifications.

